Italian Coast Guard Directs Migrant Ship Away From Collision Course
Italian authorities took control of a cargo ship carrying hundreds of migrants and deterred it from a course that would have sent it crashing into the Italian coast. Photo: Getty Images
BRINDISI, Italyâ€”The Italian coast guard early Wednesday morning boarded a cargo ship abandoned by traffickers with 970 migrants aboard and deterred it from a fast course that would have crashed it into land, authorities said.
